definition: NATO/abbr. for 北大西洋公約組織|北大西洋公约组织[Bei3 Da4 xi1 Yang2 Gong1 yue1 Zu3 zhi1], North Atlantic Treaty Organization
to make an appointment/to invite/approximately/pact/treaty/to economize/to restrict/to reduce (a fraction)/concise
to weigh in a balance or on a scale

sentences.english: Yongbyon is approximately 60 miles [96 kilometers] north of the capital at Pyongyang.
sentences.chinese: 宁边位于北韩首都平壤以北约96公里处。

sentences.english: Is Japan Planning to Create an Anti-China"Asian NATO"?
sentences.chinese: 日本打算建立一个反中国的“亚洲北约”吗？

sentences.english: In fact we need to kick Turkey out of NATO.
sentences.chinese: 事实上，我们需要把土鸡国踢出北约。

sentences.english: Miliband said the response by the European Union and NATO should be hard-headed engagement.
sentences.chinese: 米利班德说，欧盟和北约对此应该做出强硬的反应。

sentences.english: In the NATO army, the rice 124 are called "don't the deer".
sentences.chinese: 在北约军队中，米一24被称为“毋鹿”。

sentences.english: The US-led NATO forces have cordoned off the scene of the incident, witnesses said.
sentences.chinese: 目击者说北约军队在事故现场在实施了警戒。

sentences.english: Militants burn NATO fuel tankers in Pakistan.
sentences.chinese: 巴基斯坦民兵烧毁北约运油车。

sentences.english: NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer announced the decision.
sentences.chinese: 北约秘书长夏侯雅伯宣布了这一决定。

sentences.english: General Craddock will end his tour of duty later this year.
sentences.chinese: 克拉多克今年晚些时候将结束他在北约的任务。

sentences.english: I hope the U.N. will step in and provide NATO assistance to the area.
sentences.chinese: 我希望联合国将介入，并且加强北约在该地区的援助。

sentences.english: The US-led Nato recently declared that human rights are more important than national sovereignty.
sentences.chinese: 以美国为首的北约最近提出“人权高于主权”的主张。

sentences.english: The U. S. accounts for about three-quarters of total military spending by all NATO countries.
sentences.chinese: 在北约的军事开支中，美国承担了四分之一。

sentences.english: NATO soldiers took some of the wounded to a military hospital.
sentences.chinese: 北约军人把一些受伤的人送到一家军医院。

sentences.english: The NATO player is advised to utilize the terrain and engineer units to dig in.
sentences.chinese: 给北约玩家的劝告是使用地形与工兵单位去挖地洞。

sentences.english: The newcomers have also contributed militarily to NATO.
sentences.chinese: 新来者也在军事上为北约作贡献。

sentences.english: The eight trucks were transporting supplies to Nato forces in Afghanistan Photograph: Mian Khursheed/Reuters
sentences.chinese: 这是八辆为北约驻阿富汗部队运送物资的卡车。
